cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with word embeddings and their ability to capture semantic and morphological similarity. It could also belong to Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves training models to learn representations. Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding. Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) are less likely categories, but they could be relevant if the models used in the paper involve neural networks or if the evaluation measures involve visual data.
